content.description:
Sandy with poor feet. Don’t really suggest it, but the small arete feature just begs to be climbed.

Start on a cool slab with an iron hold for your right, and your left on the small arete. Work your way up off-balanced moves to the big red iron hold. A cleaner top out exists to the right, but certainly adds some difficulty. Otherwise work your way through the choss straight up, topping out next to the small tree
content.protection: Flat landing, a pad or two is helpful
content.location: Directly across from Big Iron. Follow the tab/red rock up and to the left.

content.description: Great slab problem with a slightly less than ideal landing. This problem came straight outta Joe’s Valley.
content.protection: Pad on the rock for the landing
content.location: Shares the arete with the Scoop problem, start left hand on the arete and right foot smeared on an edge on the slab about knee height. Stand up and balance your way up the low angled slab, using the arete and tiny face features.

content.description: Start in the middle of the boulder on a rail, traverse right to a big move up to a flake and top out.
content.protection: 1 pad for the top out and a spotter
content.location: Start at the far left side of the rail trending up and right.

content.description: Maybe one of the best moderate lowballs at the Park. Great rock, great movement
content.location: Walk around the backside of the boulder and find the perfectly sculpted scoop. Start low towards the right and work your way up and to the left

content.description: Start on the left side of the boulder on a rail down low with feet underneath the boulder and move up on sloped pockets to the horn for the top out. The first 3 moves are the crux which basically leaves the top out.
Fun slab route with interesting features. Delicate footwork helps
content.location: In between the two big boulders, Big Iron starts on the left side using the iron formation as a starting hold. Move up into little crimps before slapping up for the lip and topping out to the left on more iron holds.

content.description: Lowball, packs a punch though! Slap through some very cool slopers up to the good jug. Bonus points in you start in the sharp iron hold further down
content.protection: Flat landing, just a pad is good
content.location: Start on a decent edge low on the overhanging arete. Just to the left of the scoop problem.
